## Acceptance Criteria

### Phase 1 (af_range + ac_range)

- [ ] `af_range` filters variants by allele frequency using PgrGetCounts
- [ ] `ac_range` filters variants by allele count using PgrGetCounts
- [ ] Both work on `read_pfile` and `read_pgen`
- [ ] `read_pgen` computes AF/AC from .pgen header sample count (no .psam needed)
- [ ] SampleSubset built at bind time, shared across threads
- [ ] Sample subsetting: AF/AC computed on subsetted sample set
- [ ] Filters compose correctly with `region`, `variants`, and `samples`
- [ ] Validation errors for out-of-range values, min > max
- [ ] Parallel scan works correctly with af/ac filtering active (variant orient)
- [ ] `plinking_max_matrix_elements` guard applies after af/ac filtering (sample orient)
- [ ] Surviving variant set matches plink2 --freq filtered equivalently

### Phase 2 (genotype_range)

- [ ] `genotype_range` skips rows in genotype orient
- [ ] `genotype_range` nulls out elements in array/list modes (variant + sample orient)
- [ ] `genotype_range` nulls out values in columns mode (variant + sample orient)
- [ ] Missing genotypes excluded when any filter is active
- [ ] Phased mode: genotype_range applies to allele sum, nulls entire pair
- [ ] Works on both `read_pfile` and `read_pgen`

### Phase 3 (Test fixtures + scale)

- [ ] Mid-size fixture (1K×100) with hand-verified expected values
- [ ] Large fixture (30K×1K) with realistic AF distributions
- [ ] Scale tests pass with all filter combinations

